ome doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]},{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretha","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margarethe","meanings":["from Greek.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":21,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"When Margarete Beaupell was born in 1361, in Brixham, Torbay, Devon, England, her father, Sir Henry Beaupell, was 31 and her mother, Lady Elizabeth De Ether Eve, was 21. She married William Cole Esq. in 1382, in Brixham, Torbay, Devon, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1440, in her hometown, at the age of 79."},"et":{"1361–1440":"1361–1440","1355–1420":"1355–1420","1384–1473":"1384–1473","1330–1360":"1330–1360","1340–1360":"1340–1360","1440":"1440","1330":"1330","1473":"1473","1340":"1340","1384":"1384","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1359":"1359","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","after 1360":"pärast 1360","about 1384":"umbes 1384","Brixham, Torbay, Devon, Engl